data.title: Across State Lines: Gutierrez Retires

data.text:
A former Sporting Kansas City player called time on his playing career this past week. Former two time Sporting KC player, Felipe Gutierrez called time on his career in an Instagram post that he was retiring from professional soccer. Gutierrez ends a career that saw him play on four different continents over his fifteen year career. He also had an impressive international career, appearing in a World Cup and winning a Copa America with Chile.

Also this week, two former Kansas City Current players have joined clubs in Europe. First, KC native, Rylan Childers signed with Danish side, OB in the Danish second division. Also Mimmi Larsson, who mutually agreed to terminate her contract with the Current has signed in Germany with Red Bull Leipzig.

Here is the rest of this week’s update.

SKC – former Sporting KC players

ACA – former Sporting KC academy players (finished with college eligibility)

KC – Kansas City area players

SPR – former Swope Park Rangers/Sporting KC II players

Comets – former Comets players
